# ============================================================
# CODEOWNERS
#
# Each line is a file pattern followed by one or more owners.
# The last matching pattern takes precedence.
# Owners are required reviewers for PRs touching those paths.
#
# Format: <pattern> <owner> [<owner> ...]
# See: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
# ============================================================

# Global fallback — Platform Engineering team owns everything by default
*                           @your-org/platform-engineering

# Repository governance
/.github/                   @your-org/platform-engineering @your-org/engineering-leads
/CODEOWNERS                 @your-org/engineering-leads

# Infrastructure as Code — requires both platform and security review
/terraform/                 @your-org/platform-engineering @your-org/security-team
/terraform/stacks/          @your-org/platform-engineering
/terraform/modules/         @your-org/platform-engineering

# Kubernetes manifests
/kubernetes/                @your-org/platform-engineering

# Helm charts
/helm/                      @your-org/platform-engineering

# GitOps / ArgoCD
/argocd/                    @your-org/platform-engineering

# Observability stack
/monitoring/                @your-org/platform-engineering @your-org/sre-team

# CI/CD pipelines
/.github/workflows/         @your-org/platform-engineering @your-org/engineering-leads

# Documentation — lighter touch, any platform eng can approve
/docs/                      @your-org/platform-engineering
/docs/decisions/            @your-org/platform-engineering @your-org/engineering-leads

# Scripts — requires security review if touching credentials or IAM
/scripts/                   @your-org/platform-engineering @your-org/security-team
